casebody.data:
January 12, 1948.

Per Curiam Decision.

No. 449. Marden & Murphy, Inc. v. City of Lowell. Burton E. Eames for appellant-petitioner. P. Harold Ready and Raymond D. O’Brien for appellee-respondent. Per Curiam:

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question. The petition for writ of certiorari is denied.
